<div class="container">
    <h2>Welcome!</h2>
    <p>This website provides techniques and methods to help with stammering. Browse through the techniques below and try them yourself.</p>

    <div class="technique">
        <h3>Technique 1: Breathing Exercises</h3>
        <p>Practice deep breathing to calm your mind and control speech. This can help reduce stammering by focusing on a steady rhythm.</p>
        <button onclick="showDetails('breathing')">Show Details</button>
        <p id="breathing" style="display:none;">Breathe in deeply through your nose, hold for a few seconds, then exhale slowly. Repeat several times.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="technique">
        <h3>Technique 2: Slow Speaking</h3>
        <p>Slowing down your speech can allow you to better control your words and reduce stammering.</p>
        <button onclick="showDetails('slowSpeaking')">Show Details</button>
        <p id="slowSpeaking" style="display:none;">Try to speak one word at a time and take small pauses between phrases. Gradually increase your speed as you feel comfortable.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="technique">
        <h3>Technique 3: Positive Visualization</h3>
        <p>Visualize yourself speaking confidently. This can help reduce anxiety and boost confidence.</p>
        <button onclick="showDetails('visualization')">Show Details</button>
        <p id="visualization" style="display:none;">Close your eyes, picture yourself speaking fluently, and focus on that positive image before you speak.</p>
    </div>

</div>

<script>
    function showDetails(id) {
        var details = document.getElementById(id);
        if (details.style.display === "none") {
            details.style.display = "block";
        } else {
            details.style.display = "none";
        }
    }
</script>

